5: I don't really remember that day.
7:
It's all a blur. Something happened
to Shibuya, and then me and a
whole bunch of other people tried
leaving the city... which is when I
blacked out.
9:
The next thing I knew, I was waking
up in another world.
13:
How... could this happen... Is this
really Shibuya?
16:
Hibiki, I'm glad you're okay! Some
higher power must be looking out
for us, huh?
18:
Seeing you gives me hope that my
own child will return one day, safe
and sound...
20:
I guess these monsters and stuff are
pretty scary, but compared to the
way Shibuya was before, I'd rather
live here, thanks.
23:
The world had completely changed,
and everyone accepted it... except
me.
26: I was the only one left behind.
32:
Y-you're the one who wrote Binary
Planet?!
36:
I... I see. Thank you for creating such
a wonderful song. Ever since I first
heard it, I—
40:
Why is my song going to be
performed live?!
44:
It... It was a source of comfort for
Shibuyans during their days in the
emergency shelter. I was hoping to
share it with even more people, to
help—
49:
Are you kidding me? That
happened... when I wasn't around
for it...
57:
Even my own song is leaving me
behind...
61: What do I have left for myself?!
75: I'm going to go look for her!
80:
The rest of you should keep
prepping for the concert! You've got
this, Dia!
84:
Mr. Liam, Nao, could you check the
classrooms? I'll head over to the
courtyard—
88:
Oh, come on! The barrier alarm?
Now, of all times?
100:
I can't believe... I threw a tantrum...
like a stupid little kid...
104: You there. What did you do just now?
107:
Huh? Oh... I'm sorry, I didn't mean to
end up here. I'll leave right away—
110:
I asked you what you did! How did
you resonate with the serpent
sample?!
121:
The power to rewrite reality... Of
course. Procheon had the correct
hypothesis!
123:
O darkness that permeates all
creation! Fear not the light, and
unveil your might!
130:
Yes, good... Bring back the world that
you so long for!
141:
He's my attendant... He came here
with me from the Farlands.
145:
After everything we did to build trust
between the academy and
Shibuya... What is the meaning of
this?
148:
...Did my uncle put you up to this? Or
was it the Kweturs? The Oxtans?
171:
Sure, Japan had a lot more
convenient perks, but I'm just glad to
be alive. You should be too.
179:
My school is gone... My home, too,
and all of Dad's records... I can never
go back to my old life!
182:
This is the hand we were dealt, so...
gotta learn to live with it. No point
thinking about what-ifs.
185:
And how am I supposed to learn to
live with it?
188:
I have no idea what any of you went
through! I was unconscious the
whole time!
192: I can't... move on like you all are.
205: Please... I don't... want to be alone...
234:
It's gonna be all right, Hibiki! You're
not alone! We're with you, and we're
not leaving you behind!
237: Luciada, tell her what you really feel!
249:
I may not know anything about you
yet, but I love the music that you
made!
252:
Maybe I can't say for certain
whether or not Shibuya and
Palpebra can work together.
261:
I want our people to learn more
about one another!
265:
And I want to learn more about you!
Not just your other music, but all of
you!
269:
So... Hibiki! I'll stick by you... if you'll
have me!
286: How are you feeling? Can you walk?
302:
I... I didn't do much! I just blurted out
the first things that came to mind!
308: What in the world is going on?!
